# InternIQ - Cursor Rules

## Project
InternIQ: SaaS for CS students — public profile page + private AI-powered dashboard.
Stack: Next.js 14 App Router + TypeScript + shadcn/ui + Tailwind | FastAPI | Supabase | Claude API

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` types. Use `interface` for object shapes.
- Named exports (except Next.js page/layout defaults). Arrow functions for components.
- Early returns to reduce nesting. Destructure props. Template literals.
- All strings in double quotes.

## Next.js
- App Router conventions: page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.ts, loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx
- Server components by default. Only add "use client" when using hooks or browser APIs.
- API routes: export GET, POST, PUT, DELETE. Always check auth first. Use NextResponse.json().

## Supabase
- Browser client: import from src/lib/supabase/client.ts
- Server client: import from src/lib/supabase/server.ts
- Always check auth with supabase.auth.getUser() in API routes before DB operations.
- Never expose the service_role key to the client.

## Components
- UI primitives from shadcn/ui (src/components/ui/)
- Custom components in src/components/{feature}/
- cn() from src/lib/utils.ts for conditional classNames
- Every component that calls an API must have loading and error states
- Use sonner toast for success/error notifications

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS only. No inline styles. No CSS modules.
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, then sm:, md:, lg: breakpoints
- Use shadcn design tokens (bg-background, text-foreground, border-border, etc.)
